  "text": "An image of the constructed multi-channel MPI drive and detector coils is shown in Figure 5 (b) and (c) . The drive field coils were able to produce 40 mTpp field using 1.6 kW and 2.7 kW in the axial and transverse directions, respectively. This corresponds a total pFOV size of 11.4 mm along the drive field direction [CITATION_1] . Combined with additional high-inductance electromagnets along the the scanner's x-and y-cardinal directions (not shown), the scanner has a maximum x-y plane FOV of 4×4 cm. The z-axis FOV can be arbitrarily long for typical scans, as the animal is translated relative to the FFR via the use of a robot stage along the z-axis akin to computed tomography techniques.",
